com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.step

Class StepProperty

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.step.StepProperty

  • public class StepProperty
extends Object
    Class that represents a single step property - an item displayed in the UI within the step's panel, either displaying information about the step, or allowing the user to configure it. Property configuration is fluid, and is reactive to the user's actions within the UI, so configuration of a property is performed the creator of the property, typically by setting function handlers for the appropriate attributes.

        public StepProperty withIconTypeSupplier(Function<StepProperty,Supplier<Object>> iconForGivenSP)
        Provides a function handler that will get the icon for the property. The icon will be displayed in the UI next to the property. The handler will return a string indicating the icon to be used. See IconType or the documentation for a list of valid icons. The handler will be called when the state of the property changes.
        Parameters:
        iconForGivenSP - hander returning an object, currently the icon name as a string.

        StepProperty, for chaining calls together
